    "summary": "\"The world is big and I want to have a good look at it before it gets dark.\"\n- John Muir\nAdd a splash of education to this quote and it becomes my favourite construction of words.\nEver since I was a child, education, travel, languages and writing have been my passion. Nothing much has changed since then\u2026..internationalisation of (higher) education runs through my veins.\nI grew up at a hotel on a Caribbean island and most of my closest friends visited once a year, penpalling was the social media of that era. A letter from a friend in Spain, Germany, the USA or France was more than just a letter; it was:\n\u2022\tthe beginning of my desire to travel to the destination of the letter\u2019s origin\n\u2022\teagerness to learn more about mother tongues other than English and the seemingly difficult task of some of my friends\u2019 letters written in their second language\nAt the age of 17 I began to satisfy these desires all in one go. Subconsciously a product of internationalisation myself, I immersed myself in international education, the English language, \ncurriculum development, testing and evaluation, educational technology and instructional design for online learning.\n\nA day in my life is never boring, that\u2019s a guarantee! If you would be my work buddy for a day, you could find yourself doing one or more of the following:\n\u2022\tWorking on policy for international education and internationalisation\n\u2022\tDeveloping curricula for higher education\n\u2022\tAssessing English exams using the Common European Framework of Languages or self-developed rubrics\n\u2022\tTransferring knowledge on how to communicate using Business English\n\u2022\tSpeaking at a conference or workshop locally or abroad\n\u2022\tCreating, writing and developing scripts as part of eLearning content\n\u2022\tCopywriting/Proofreading in English\n\u2022\tVirtually or physically exploring the world\n\u2022\tHaving a good laugh with colleagues\n\u2022\tResponding to my teenagers\u2019 calls and messages\n\nIn my free time you can find me in a dance studio, reading a good old-fashioned book or on Netflix.\n\nI enjoy meeting new people and hearing new perspectives. Feel free to reach out if you would like to talk about anything mentioned in my profile or a general chat on education.\n\nProfessional skills\nInternationalisation | International Education| Curriculum Development |English-language assessments| Public Speaking| Educational Policy| Copywriting| \nProofreading |eLearning| Instructional Design| Business English\n\n",
